<lb/><p><placeName>12 Kensington Palace Gardens</placeName></p>
<lb/><p rend="right">18<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">th</hi></hi> January 1858</p>
<lb/><p>My Dear <persName>Sir</persName></p>
<lb/><p>I have been hoping 
<lb/>to avail myself 
<lb/>of your kind 
<lb/>invitation to visit 
<lb/>you and get some 
<lb/>instruction as to the 

	<pb n="0002" facs="liv_001179_0002"/><!--pb/@n='2'--> 
<lb/>use of an instrument 
<lb/>for determining the 
<lb/>Longitude which 
<lb/>you recommended, 
<lb/>but being so 
<lb/>much bothered 
<lb/>by the Admiralty as 
<lb/>to have no time 
<lb/>I can call my 
<lb/>own, I think 
<lb/>it will be facilitating 
<lb/>business if you 

	<pb n="0003" facs="liv_001179_0003"/><!--pb/@n='3'--> 
<lb/>would kindly tell 
<lb/>me about the 
<lb/>Instrument - its 
<lb/>probable cost &amp; 
<lb/>size, and if my 
<lb/>funds will reach 
<lb/>it I will set 
<lb/>about getting it 
<lb/>as soon as 
<lb/>possible.</p>
<lb/><p>I hope to get 
<lb/>away next <del type="strikethrough" resp="#CO">week</del> month 

	<pb n="0004" facs="liv_001179_0004"/><!--pb/@n='4'--> 
<lb/><!--Hand 02 91798 top right-->but the vessel is 
<lb/>not yet quite fixed 
<lb/>upon which is to 
<lb/>carry us out.</p>
<lb/><p>With kindest regards 
<lb/>to M<hi rend="sup"><hi rend="underline">rs</hi></hi> S.</p>
<lb/><p rend="center">I am yours &amp;c</p>
<lb/><p>David Livingstone</p>
<lb/><p><persName>Admiral <choice><sic>Smythe</sic><corr>Smyth</corr></choice></persName></p><!-- Hand 03 Sotheby. 12.12.22. bottom left--><!-- Hand 03 16257. bottom centre-->
			
